# Template for the SEMI-AUTOMATED token refresh (refresh_token_semi.py).
# Copy to config/upstox_app.env (gitignored) and fill in. These are your
# developer *app* credentials only - NOT your account password/PIN/TOTP.
# On their own they cannot log in or mint a token; every refresh still
# requires you to log in through the browser.
#
# UPSTOX_CLIENT_ID=your-api-key
# UPSTOX_CLIENT_SECRET=your-api-secret
# UPSTOX_REDIRECT_URI=https://your-registered-redirect-uri
#
# Optional: auto-push the fresh token to the Oracle VM after each refresh.
# Leave blank/omit to just write config/token.txt locally.
# VM_SSH_HOST=ubuntu@140.238.226.69
# VM_SSH_KEY=../ssh-key-2026-07-19.key
# VM_TOKEN_PATH=paper/config/token.txt
#
# Tip: if you register a localhost redirect URI (e.g. http://localhost:5000/),
# the script captures the code automatically with no copy-paste.
